---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
const updated = 'July 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service — SNAG" description="The terms that govern use of the SNAG application and website.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-ink">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-3">Last updated {updated} · <em>Draft — pending legal review</em></p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-2">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">1. The service</h2>
      <p>
        SNAG is an issue and health &amp; safety reporting tool provided by
        {SITE.company}. During early access the service is provided as-is and
        features may change as we develop the product with our first customers.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">2. Your account and content</h2>
      <p>
        You are responsible for the accuracy of the information you submit and
        for keeping your login secure. Content reported into an organisation
        belongs to that organisation. You must have the right to share any
        photos or information you upload.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">3. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        Don't use SNAG to harass, defame, or submit knowingly false reports;
        don't attempt to access another organisation's data; don't interfere
        with the operation of the service.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">4. Not a substitute for compliance</h2>
      <p>
        SNAG supports your health &amp; safety processes but does not replace
        your legal obligations under the Health and Safety at Work Act 2015
        (NZ), the model WHS laws (AU), or any other applicable law — including
        obligations to notify regulators of notifiable events.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">5. Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, {SITE.company}'s liability in
        connection with the service is limited to the amount you have paid for
        it in the preceding 12 months. Nothing in these terms limits rights
        you have under the Consumer Guarantees Act 1993 (NZ) or Australian
        Consumer Law that cannot be excluded.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">6. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms; we'll give reasonable notice of material
        changes. Continued use after changes take effect constitutes
        acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">Contact</h2>
      <p>{SITE.company} · {SITE.contactEmail}</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
